-- Summary 2: Fixed type errors: predicates that used Interface (Account_Settings_Page) as a target Resource were corrected by adding a concrete ProfileResource sig and replacing references accordingly.
-- Summary 3: Safety and liveness assertions cover authorization, resource access, well-formedness, and post-state reachability.
-- Summary 4: Non-functional invariants constrain channel count and scalability.
-- Assumption 1: Error conditions (photo >2MB, biography >500 chars) are represented by unencrypted or unauthenticated channel attributes as proxies.
-- Assumption 2: The profile resource is modeled as one specific Resource (ProfileResource) distinct from the UI interface.
-- Assumption 3: Size and biography length are abstracted away; edge cases are commented out due to missing fields.
-- Assumption 4: The system has exactly six actor roles as defined.
-- Open issue 1: Edge case assertions for size and biography length are commented out and not checked; they require additional fields to be added to Resource.
-- Open issue 2: The model uses proxy attributes (encrypted, authenticated) to represent error conditions, which is an over-simplification.
